35. Component Diagram Creation
The component diagram represents the high-level software architecture of the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System. It illustrates how major system components interact with each other to support incident reporting, severity assessment, response coordination, monitoring, and compliance management.
Identified Components
User Interface (Employee Portal, SOC Dashboard & Admin Console)
Provides interfaces for employees to report incidents, SOC teams to manage responses, and administrators to monitor system performance.
Incident Reporting Module
Captures incident details submitted by users and validates the input before forwarding it for analysis.
Severity Classification & Risk Analysis Module
Automatically evaluates reported incidents and assigns severity levels based on predefined rules and threat indicators.
Incident Management & Response Workflow Module
Manages incident lifecycle stages, including assignment, investigation, mitigation, escalation, and closure.
Notification & Alert Service
Sends real-time alerts and updates to employees, SOC analysts, and administrators through multiple communication channels.
Reporting & Compliance Module
Generates incident reports, audit logs, compliance documentation, and performance analytics.
Authentication & Authorization Module
Ensures secure access control by verifying user identities and enforcing role-based permissions.
Centralized Incident Database
Stores incident records, user data, response actions, audit trails, and historical analytics.
